HEADWORD: Creese
<hw>Creese</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Malay.
<ets>kris</ets>.]</ety> <def>A dagger or short sword used by the Malays,
commonly having a serpentine blade.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>crease</asp> and <asp>kris</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From a Malayan <qex>creese</qex> to a sailor's jackknife.</q>
<rj><qau>Julian Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cremaillere</ent>⟦br⟧
